                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d156">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">462.00 R 29/2267: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Herrick</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-12-28T17:00:00+00:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 28, 1922—5 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received 6:45 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>544. B–818. Our B–816.<note n="31" xml:id="d156fn31">
                        <hi rend="italic">Supra.</hi>
                    </note> In final text of decision given interpretation word “default” paragraph
                    17, annex 2, reference to paragraph 18, same annex, is deleted and “default” is
                    simply defined as signifying “voluntary default.” Boyden.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Herrick</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
